OL,3,CGrandmother's 'treasured items' binned
OL,4,Cby contractors who 'thought she was
OL,5,Cdead'
OL,7,F"I know it's not about the value of
OL,8,Fhow much it was. It's just what's
OL,9,Fhappened and that's been taken away
OL,10,Ffrom us."
OL,12,FDespite efforts from the family and
OL,13,Fthe insurer to track down the items,
OL,14,Fit's thought they have been lost
OL,15,Fforever.
OL,17,FAmong the items lost are Mabel's photo
OL,18,Falbums and love letters between her
OL,19,Fand her late husband, all
OL,20,Firreplaceable.
