OL,3,CGrandmother's 'treasured items' binned
OL,4,Cby contractors who 'thought she was
OL,5,Cdead'
OL,7,F"I don't know how I could tell her",
OL,8,FKaren added. "How could you tell a 97
OL,9,Fyear old that all her husband's
OL,10,Fpossessions have gone? The love
OL,11,Fletters that she used to talk about,
OL,12,Fher jewellery, everything."
OL,14,FA spokesperson for RSA Insurance told
OL,15,FITV Meridian: "We are sincerely sorry
OL,16,Ffor the upset caused to Mrs Ogle and
OL,17,Fher granddaughter Mrs Henshaw when
OL,18,Fsome of Mrs Ogle's belongings were
OL,19,Fincorrectly disposed of during the
OL,20,Fhandling of the water damage to her
OL,21,Fhome.
